 largely confined to Scotland. In the 20th century it became more widely used in the English-speaking world and enjoyed a period of great popularity, but it is now out of fashion. Among numerous well-known and influential bearers are the British novelists  Jean Plaidy  (  Eleanor Hibbert ,  1910–93 ) and  Jean Rhys  (  Ella Gwendolen Rees Williams ,  1894–1979 ), British actress  Jean Simmons  (  1929–2010 ), and American-born actress  Jean Seberg  (  1938–79 ). It is also found as a variant spelling of the masculine name   Gene ."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."]},{"name":"Jeane","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Jean ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Jean de Raineval I was born about 1240, in France, his father, Raoul I de Raineval, was 36 and his mother, Avicie de Nanteuil-le-Haudoin, was 31. He married Isabelle de Beaumetz. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. He died after 1325."},"et":{"Abt 1240–after 1325":"umbes 1240–pärast 1325","1228–Female":"1228–Surnud","1240–1325":"1240–1325","1232–1298":"1232–1298","1270–1329":"1270–1329","1290–1339":"1290–1339","1291–1365":"1291–1365","1205–1265":"1205–1265","1210–Female":"1210–Surnud","about 1270":"umbes 1270","1240":"1240","1270":"1270","1291":"1291","1290":"1290","1228":"1228","Abt 1240":"umbes 1240","after 1325":"pärast 1325","1205":"1205","1226":"1226","1325":"1325","1365":"1365","1265":"1265","1298":"1298","1210":"1210","1232":"1232","Abt 1290":"umbes 1290","1329":"1329","1339":"1339","Mailly-Raineval, Somme, Picardie, France":"Mailly-Raineval, Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Nanteuil-le-Haudouin, Senlis, Oise, Picardie, France":"Nanteuil-le-Haudouin, Senlis, Oise, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"Abt 1240–after 1325":"noin 1240–1325 jälkeen","1228–Female":"1228–Kuollut","1240–1325":"1240–1325","1232–1298":"1232–1298","1270–1329":"1270–1329","1290–1339":"1290–1339","1291–1365":"1291–1365","1205–1265":"1205–1265","1